;Firefox can tell websites where you’re located so you can find info that’s more relevant and more useful. It’s about making the Web smarter &ndash; and is done in a way that totally respects your privacy. <a href="%(url)s" id="%(id)s" style="%(style)s">Give it a try!</a>
Firefox po dir a websites nua che ti ta chattas, uschia che ti survegns infurmaziuns pli relevantas e pli utilas. Il web daventa pli raffinà e tia sfera privata vegn tuttina respectada. <a href="%(url)s" id="%(id)s" style="%(style)s">Emprova!</a>


;Frequently asked Questions
Dumondas frequentas


;What is Location-Aware Browsing?
Tge è Location-Aware Browsing?


;Websites that use location-aware browsing will ask where you are in order to bring you more relevant information, or to save you time while searching. Let’s say you’re looking for a pizza restaurant in your area. A website will be able to ask you to share your location so that simply searching for “pizza” will bring you the answers you need... no further information or extra typing required.
Websites che utiliseschan il Location-Aware Browsing vegnan a dumandar tai nua che ti ta chattas cun l’intenziun da pudair porscher a tai infurmaziuns pli relevantas e da ta gidar a spargnar temp da tschertgar. Ti tschertgas per exempel ina pizzeria en tes conturn. Ina website vegn ad esser abla da dumandar tai da communitgar tia posiziun uschia ch’i basta da tschertgar «pizza» per survegnir las respostas che ti dovras – senza ulteriuras infurmaziuns e senza tippar dapli.


;Or, if you’re mapping out directions to get somewhere, the website will know where you’re starting from so all you have to do is tell it where you want to go.
U sche ti vuls planisar in viadi vegn la website a savair danunder che ti partas. I basta da simplamain inditgar nua che ti vuls ir.


;This service is totally optional &ndash; Firefox doesn’t share your location without your permission &ndash; and is done with the utmost respect for your privacy. And, like all elements of Firefox, it’s being created using open standards to ease adoption by Web developers.
Quest servetsch è cumplettamain voluntar – Firefox na vegn mai a communitgar tia posiziun senza tes consentiment – e tia sfera privata vegn respectada il meglier pussaivel. E sco tut ils elements da Firefox è questa funcziun vegnida creada cun standards averts per simplifitgar l’introducziun per programmaders dal web.


;How does it work?
Sco funcziuni?


;When you visit a location-aware website, Firefox will ask you if you want to share your location.
Sche ti visitas ina website Location-Aware, vegn Firefox a dumandar sche ti vuls communitgar tia posiziun.


;If you consent, Firefox gathers information about nearby wireless access points and your computer’s IP address. Then Firefox sends this information to the default geolocation service provider, Google Location Services, to get an estimate of your location. That location estimate is then shared with the requesting website.
Sche ti es d’accord, rimna Firefox infurmaziuns davart puncts d'access wireless en tia vischinanza e l’adressa IP da tes computer. Lura trametta Firefox questa infurmaziun al purschider da servetschs da geolocalisaziun da standard, Google Location Services, per retschaiver ina calculaziun approximativa da tia posiziun. Questa posiziun stimada vegn lura tramessa a la website.


;If you say that you do not consent, Firefox will not do anything.
Sche ti dis che ti na sajas betg d’accord, na fa Firefox nagut.


;How accurate are the locations?
Quant exactas èn las posiziuns?


;Accuracy varies greatly from location to location. In some places, our service providers may be able to provide a location to within a few meters. However, in other areas it might be much more than that. All locations returned by our service providers are estimates only and we do not guarantee the accuracy of the locations provided. Please do not use this information for emergencies. Always use common sense.
L’exactadad variescha fermamain d’in lieu a l’auter. En tschertas localitads pon ils purschiders da noss servetschs definir la posiziun fin a paucs meters. En in auter lieu po la stimaziun esser bler pli inexacta. Tut las posiziuns che noss purschiders da servetschs tramettan enavos restan stimaziuns, nus na pudain betg garantir l’exactadad da las indicaziuns. N’utilisescha betg questas infurmaziuns en cas d'urgenza. Dovra adina il saun giudizi.


;What information is being sent, and to whom? How is my privacy protected?
Tge infurmaziuns vegnan tramessas ed a tgi vegnan ellas tramessas? Sco vegn mia sfera privata protegida?


;Your privacy is extremely important to us, and Firefox never shares your location without your permission. When you visit a page that requests your information, you’ll be asked before any information is shared with the requesting website and our third-party service provider.
Tia sfera privata è ordvart impurtanta per nus e Firefox na tradescha mai tia posiziun senza tes consentiment. Sche ti visitas ina pagina che dumonda questa infurmaziun, vegns ti dumandà avant che x-ina infurmaziun vegn tramessa a la website respectiva u a noss purschider da servetschs.


;By default, Firefox uses Google Location Services to determine your location by sending:
Tenor la configuraziun predefinida utilisescha Firefox Google Location Services per determinar tia posiziun cun trametter:


;your computer’s IP address,
l’adressa IP da tes computer,


;information about the nearby wireless access points, and
infurmaziuns davart ils puncts d’access wireless damanaivels, ed


;a random client identifier, which is assigned by Google, that expires every 2 weeks.
in identificatur casual dal client che vegn assegnà da Google e scroda mintga duas emnas.


;For a complete description of information collected and used by Firefox, please see the <a href="%(url)s">Firefox Privacy Notice</a>.
Legia <a href="%(url)s">las directivas davart la protecziun da datas da Firefox</a> (per englais) per ina descripziun cumpletta da las infurmaziuns rimnadas ed utilisadas da Firefox.


;Google Location Services then returns your estimated geolocation (e.g., latitude and longitude). For a complete description of information collected and used by Google, please see the <a href="%(url)s" class="%(class)s">Google Geolocation Privacy Policy</a>.
Google Location Services trametta lura enavos tia posiziun geografica stimada (vul dir: grad da ladezza e grad da longhituda). Legia <a href="%(url)s" class="%(class)s">la Google Geolocation Privacy Policy</a> (per englais) per ina descripziun cumpletta da las infurmaziuns rimnadas ed utilisadas da Google.


;The information is exchanged over an encrypted connection to protect your privacy. Once Firefox has your location information, it passes it to the website that requested it. At no time is the name or location of the website you are visiting, or are any cookies, ever shared with Google Location Services.
L’infurmaziun vegn tramessa cun agid d’ina connexiun criptada per proteger tia sfera privata. Sche Firefox ha retschavì l’infurmaziun davart tia posiziun, vegn quella dada vinavant a la website che l’ha dumandà. Il num, l’adressa da la website che ti visitas u cookies na vegnan mai tradids a Google Location Services.


;Neither Mozilla or Google will ever use the information collected by Google Location Services to identify or spy on you.
Ni Mozilla ni Google na vegnan era mai ad utilisar las infurmaziuns rimnadas da Google Location Services per identifitgar u spiunar tai.


;For information about what the requesting website does with your location information, please refer to that website’s privacy policy.
Infurmaziuns davart la dumonda co che tias datas vegnan utilisadas da la website che dumonda tia posiziun geografica chattas ti en las directivas davart la protecziun da datas da la website respectiva.


;For more information about your privacy, you should also read:
Dapli infurmaziuns davart tia sfera privata survegns ti qua:


;Mozilla Firefox Privacy Notice
Decleraziun da protecziun da datas Mozilla Firefox


;Google privacy policy
Decleraziun da protecziun da datas Google


;Am I being tracked as I browse the web?
Vegn jau registrà, sche jau navighesch en l’internet?


;No. Firefox only requests a location when a website makes a request, and only shares your location when the user has approved the request. Firefox does not track or remember your location as you browse.
Na. Firefox dumonda mo ina posiziun, sch'ina website dumonda ina tala e tradescha mo tia posiziun sche l’utilisader ha approvà la dumonda. Firefox ni registrescha ni memorisescha tia posiziun, sche ti navigheschas en l’internet.


;How do I undo a permission granted to a site?
Co poss jau revocar ina permissiun concedida ad ina website?


;If you've given Firefox permission to always give your location to a site and later change your mind, you can easily revoke that permission. Here's how:
